JOHANNESBURG - ANC Treasurer General Paul Mashatile says that the phones of most party leaders are probably bugged. Mashatile was responding to allegations by ANC Secretary General Ace Magashule. Magashule recently claimed that his phone is bugged. READ: Zuma helped start ATM: report Mashatile said that it is suspected that the entire leadership of the party is being followed. “Most of us, our phones are bugged anyway,” Mashatile said. “There are a lot of people that are interested in you, there are a lot of agencies out there, you can’t assume it is one particular agent.” WATCH: ANC expecting over 100,000 people at Siyanqoba rally Mashatile also said the party is focused on the election and not on allegations against senior members. He was responding to reports that Magashule and former president Jacob Zuma helped form the African Transformation Movement (ATM).